  "prompt": "I have got 986 rank in BHU UET test for BA social science, will I get admission in BA social?",
  "response": "Securing a rank of 986 in the BHU UET (Banaras Hindu University Undergraduate Entrance Test) for BA Social Sciences depends on several factors, including the total number of seats available, the cutoff ranks from previous years, and the competition level this year. Here\u2019s how you can assess your chances:\n\n### Steps to Assess Your Admission Chances:\n1. **Check the Total Number of Seats**: Look up the total number of seats available for BA Social Sciences in BHU. This information is usually available on the official BHU website or the admission brochure.\n\n2. **Analyze Previous Year Cutoffs**: Review the cutoff ranks for BA Social Sciences from the past 2\u20133 years. This will give you an idea of the rank range that usually gets admission. If your rank is within or better than this range, you have a good chance.\n\n3. **Consider This Year\u2019s Competition**: If the number of applicants has increased significantly this year or if the exam was relatively easier, the cutoff rank might be higher. Conversely, if the competition is lower, the cutoff could be more favorable.\n\n4. **Wait for the Merit List**: The official merit list released by BHU will confirm your admission status. Keep checking the BHU admission portal for updates.\n\n### General Observations (Based on past trends):\n- For BA Social Sciences in BHU, ranks within **1\u20131500** often have a good chance of admission, depending on seat availability and category (general/OBC/SC/ST).\n- If your rank is 986, you have a fair chance of getting admission, provided the cutoff rank for this year is similar to previous years.\n\n### What You Can Do Now:\n- **Stay Updated**: Monitor the BHU admission portal for the merit list and counseling schedule.\n- **Prepare for Counseling**: Gather all required documents (rank card, certificates, ID proof, etc.) in advance.\n- **Consider Backup Options**: If you\u2019re unsure about BHU, explore other universities or courses as a backup.\n\nGood luck! Let me know if you need further assistance.",
